-- India’s Crude Oil Output Rose 0.5% to 3.2 Million Tons in May
-- B y   R a k t e e m   K a t a k e y
-- 2012-06-27T09:30:00Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-06-27/india-s-crude-oil-output-rose-0-5-to-3-2-million-tons-in-may.html
India ’s crude oil production rose
0.5 percent to 3.2 million metric tons in May, the oil ministry
said.  Output by Oil & Natural Gas Corp., the nation’s biggest
exploration company, fell 4.1 percent to 1.9 million tons, the
ministry said in an e-mailed statement today. The nation’s
natural gas production dropped 10.8 percent to 3.7 billion cubic
meters, according to the ministry.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Rakteem Katakey in New Delhi at 
